[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged after prisoner transport van overturns on A952

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged after a prisoner transport van overturned on an Aberdeenshire road.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Four people - one prisoner and three G4S staff - were taken to hospital for treatment after the crash on the A952 at Cortes in October.
The van had been travelling between Fraserburgh and Aberdeen.
Police Scotland said a 49-year-old man had been charged in connection with the incident and reported to the procurator fiscal.
